@title Clock auction modified for sale of Cell tokens
@param _address - Address to receive proceeds of auctions created by core contract
@dev Allows an operator to retrieve funds from the contract into the finance account

@dev Updates lastDiscoveredCellSalePrices if seller is the Cell contract
 Otherwise, works the same as default bid method.

bid(uint256).details: Updates lastDiscoveredCellSalePrices if seller is the Cell contract Otherwise, works the same as default bid method.

cancelAuction(uint256).details: Cancels an auction that hasn't been won yet     Returns the token to its original owner

params._duration: - Length of time (in seconds) to move between the         starting price and the ending price
params._endingPrice: - Final price (in wei) the auction can reach
params._seller: - The listed seller for the auction (the token owner         can set someone else as the seller/beneficiary)
params._startingPrice: - Starting price (in wei) at beginning of auction
params._tokenId: - ID of token to auction, sender must be its owner

getAuction(uint256).details: Returns the data for an auction

params._tokenId: - ID of the token being auction

getCurrentPrice(uint256).details: Returns the current price of an auction

params._tokenId: - ID of the token on auction

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

retrieveFunds().details: Allows an operator to retrieve funds from the contract into the finance account

params._address: - Address to receive proceeds of auctions created by core contract
